        <body>
            <p>The present study conducted a comparative analysis of business models used by ESCOs, contributing to dealing with split-incentive issues to develop a new ESCO business model. The study also provided recommendations for enhanced energy service in the commercial sector, and the proposed model was implemented in Greece, Ireland, and Spain. The present study's main flaw is using the research method for comparative business models. The following comments would improve the acceptability of the present research.</p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> 
                <bold>Abstract</bold>
            </p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> Results should be presented briefly in the abstract.</p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> 
                <bold>Introduction</bold>
            </p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> Please dedicate a paragraph to contributions. The contributions of the study are not clear or hard to follow.</p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> The article's structure should be presented at the end of the introduction.</p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> 
                <bold>Methods</bold>
            </p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> Surprisingly, there is no clear information regarding the research steps. For instance, which features of business models were considered in comparative analysis? How did the authors interview the experts? How did the authors validate the collected data through interviews? Overall, the research method's steps should be explained clearly and followed quickly by readers. It is recommended to provide a flow chart illustrating the research steps. Also, the authors should explain why they implemented the proposed business model in Greece, Ireland, and Spain.</p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> 
                <bold>Sections 3, 4, and 5</bold>
            </p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> Well presented.</p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> 
                <bold>Conclusions</bold>
            </p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> Any limitations to the present study?</p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> Provide some accurate recommendations for future studies.</p>
            <p>Is the study design appropriate and does the work have academic merit?</p>
            <p>Partly</p>
            <p>Is the work clearly and accurately presented and does it cite the current literature?</p>
            <p>Partly</p>
            <p>If applicable, is the statistical analysis and its interpretation appropriate?</p>
            <p>Partly</p>
            <p>Are all the source data underlying the results available to ensure full reproducibility?</p>
            <p>Partly</p>
